description.plain:
Melii, born December 31, 1997, is a Dominican rapper from Harlem, New York.

Melii started putting music out online in 2017 with the single “No Simple Chick” but didn’t gain widespread exposure until the release of her 2018 single “Icey.”

In 2019, Melii was signed to Tory Lanez' One Umbrella.

description.plain:

Melii announced the song on social media a day before its release:

description.plain:
Melii, a new Dominican rapper comes out strong with her fresh remix of Cardi B’s Bodak Yellow.

She exhibits her vocal talent in singing, and flow switching as she raps in English and in Spanish on this track. Also, she expresses a unique and very one-of-a-kind swagger on this track and challenges any comparisons to Cardi, Nicki, or Remy.

description.plain:
“No Simple Chick” is the debut single from Melii, which gained more attention following her bilingual remix of Cardi B’s “Bodak Yellow,” despite being released before that.

In the song, Melii sings about enjoying the simple pleasures in life, but she doesn’t want men to confuse that with her being a simple person.
